{"word":"H8277 - שָׂרַד - sârad - saw-rad' - Remain","slug":"H8277","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שָׂרַד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>sârad"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>saw-rad'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Remain"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C2;&#x05E8;&#x05D3; - s&#x0301;a&#x0302;rad</b> - <i>saw-rad'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>puncture</i> (compare <a href=\"#/H8279\">H8279</a>), that is, (figuratively through the idea of <i>slipping</i> out) to <i>escape</i> or survive: - remain."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8300\">H8300</a>, <a href=\"#/H8301\">H8301</a>"}]}